# Assignment4

# Instruction to Run and Execute

## After cloning the repository

### Setting Up API server

1. First of install virtualenv in conda environment using command : conda install virtualenv
2. create virtual environment using the command : virtualenv venv --python=python3.8
3. Activate the virtual env using the command : source venv/bin/activate
4. Install the required library
   Method - 1 : using the command : pip install flask flask_RESTful flask-JWT flask_sqlalchemy
   Method - 2 : using the requirement.txt file : pip install -r requirement.txt

### Running the server

1. Move to code folder
2. Open the terminal and move to the folder containing the app.py file and run it using the command : python app.py to start the database server

# Angular

Note : This project was generated with [Angular CLI](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli) version 14.1.0.

1. As of next step open the "Angular App" folder in an intergrated terminal and then run the command
   `npm install` to install all the dependencies and other requirements.
2. To start the server run the command `ng serve` or `npm start`
3. Navigate to `http://localhost:4200/` in chrome browser.
4. Register and then login.
